============================================================================
## 04 VALIDATION SYSTEM
============================================================================
## What it does: Checks user input before saving to database.
## MVP scope: Format validation only (types, ranges, required fields).
## Why it matters: Prevents garbage data. Shows Django forms integration.
============================================================================

## <<service>> ValidationService
## Not a database table - this is a utility class with validation logic.
## Called by FallManager before saving any entity.
<<service>> ValidationService:
+ validateInput(input_data, field_name, field_type) : ValidationResult
+ validatePassword(password) : boolean  ## Min length, requires digit/special char
+ validateDate(date_string) : boolean  ## Format check (YYYY-MM-DD)
+ validateNumber(number_string) : boolean  ## Is it actually a number?
+ validateEnum(value, allowed_values) : boolean  ## Is value in the list?

## MVP Implementation Notes:
## - validateInput() is the main entry point - checks one field at a time
## - field_type determines which specific validator to call
## - Returns ValidationResult with pass/fail and error messages
## - Django forms will call this on form.is_valid()

## Example Usage in FallManager:
## result = ValidationService.validateInput(data['alter'], 'alter', 'int')
## if not result.is_valid:
##     return result.error_messages

## ValidationResult
## Container for validation outcomes. Created by ValidationService.
ValidationResult:
- is_valid : boolean  ## True = all checks passed
- error_messages : List<string>  ## Empty if valid, otherwise reasons for failure
+ addError(error) : void  ## Append a new error message
+ getSummary() : string  ## Joins all error messages with newlines

## MVP Example:
## result = ValidationResult()
## result.is_valid = False
## result.addError("Alter muss zwischen 0 und 120 liegen")
## result.addError("Pflichtfeld darf nicht leer sein")
## print(result.getSummary())
## â†’ "Alter muss zwischen 0 und 120 liegen\nPflichtfeld darf nicht leer sein"
